\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \'93Well, Prince, so Genoa and Lucca are now just family estates of the Buonapartes. But I warn you, if you don\'92t tell me that this means war, if you still try to defend the infamies and horrors perpetrated by that Antichrist\'97I really believe he is Antichrist\'97I will have nothing more to do with you and you are no longer my friend, no longer my \'91faithful slave,\'92 as you call yourself! But how do you do? I see I have frightened you\'97sit down and tell me all the news.\'94\
It was in July, 1805, and the speaker was the well-known Anna P\'e1vlovna Sch\'e9rer, maid of honor and favorite of the Empress M\'e1rya F\'ebdorovna. With these words she greeted Prince Vas\'edli Kur\'e1gin, a man of high rank and importance, who was the first to arrive at her reception. Anna P\'e1vlovna had had a cough for some days. She was, as she said, suffering from\'a0
\f1\i la grippe; grippe
